  • Method Details

    • testSetLibrary

      @Test void testSetLibrary()
      Tests both the setLibrary() and getLibrary() methods.

      Tests the initial value, that library cannot be passed as a null object and that when passed a library object the library data member updates.

    • testSetDeviceId

      @Test void testSetDeviceId()
      Tests both the setDeviceId() and the getDeviceId() methods.

      Tests the initial value, an allowed value, an Id identical to that of a device already in the library, and too shot and too long strings.

    • testSetDeviceLocation

      @Test void testSetDeviceLocation()
      Tests both the setDeviceLocation() and getDeviceLocation() methods.

      Tests initial value and that when passed a string the deviceLocation updates.

    • testSetDeviceType

      @Test void testSetDeviceType()
      Tests both the setDeviceType() and the getDeviceType() methods.

      Tests initial value and that when passed a string the deviceType updates.

    • testSetIsAvailable

      @Test void testSetIsAvailable()
      Tests both the isAvailable() and setIsAvailable() methods.

      Tests the initial value and then that when passed a new boolean that isAvailable updates.
